# Media Toolkit - Project Rules

## Versioning

When making changes, update the version in these files (must be aligned):
1. `media-toolkit.php` - Header "Version:" (line 9) and constant `MEDIA_TOOLKIT_VERSION` (line 31)
2. `package.json` - "version" field (line 3)

Use semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH):
- PATCH: bug fixes, minor corrections
- MINOR: new backwards-compatible features
- MAJOR: breaking changes

## Documentation

When modifying code, also update:
1. `README.md` - Changelog and features
2. `docs/DOCUMENTATION.md` - Detailed documentation
3. `docs/HOOKS.md` - If adding/modifying hooks and filters
4. `docs/EXTENDING.md` - If adding new extension possibilities

## Build Assets

After changes to CSS/JS in `assets/src/`, run:
```bash
npm run build
```

## Code Structure

- PHP 8.2+ with strict types
- Namespace: `Metodo\MediaToolkit`
- PSR-4 autoloading
- WordPress coding standards

## Module Structure

The plugin is organized into modules:
- `src/Admin/` - Admin pages and settings
- `src/S3/` - Amazon S3 offloading
- `src/CDN/` - CDN integration (CloudFront, Cloudflare)
- `src/Media/` - Image optimization and processing
- `src/Migration/` - Media migration tools
- `src/Stats/` - Statistics and reporting
- `src/History/` - Action history logging

